@node Bedienung

  I. Using Drop'n Act V2
  ----------------------

    You control the preferences editor of Drop'n Act via three windows:

    @{"I.I   The Type-Window     " LINK TypFenster} you see after starting
    @{"I.II  The Edit-Window     " LINK EditFenster} in which you can edit
                                 filetypes and
    @{"I.III The Command-Window  " LINK Kommandos} in which you can choose
                                 commands for filetype-scripts.

    All parts of the preferences editor can be controlled by keyboard or
  by mouse.

  @{"Back to main menu" LINK MAIN}
@endnode

@node TypFenster

  I.I. The Type-Window
  --------------------

    The Type-Window is the window which you see after starting the
  program. Here, you see a list of all filetypes known to Drop'n Act
  as well as twelve gadgets.

    @{"I.I.I.    The Filetype-List   " LINK Typenliste}
    @{"I.I.II.   Top                 " LINK Erstes}
    @{"I.I.III.  Bottom              " LINK Letztes}
    @{"I.I.IV.   Up                  " LINK Hoch}
    @{"I.I.V.    Down                " LINK Runter}
    @{"I.I.VI.   Add                 " LINK TypNeu}
    @{"I.I.VII.  Remove              " LINK LoescheTyp}
    @{"I.I.VIII. Edit                " LINK Edieren}
    @{"I.I.IX.   Shell               " LINK Shell}
    @{"I.I.X.    Save                " LINK Save}
    @{"I.I.XI.   Use                 " LINK Use}
    @{"I.I.XII.  Cancel              " LINK Cancel}
    @{"I.I.XIII. IconPos             " LINK Icon}


  @{"Back to the menu 'Using Drop'n Act V2'" LINK Bedienung}
  @{"Back to the main menu                 " LINK MAIN}
@endnode

@node Typenliste

  I.I.I. The list "Filetypes"
  ---------------------------

  Shortcut: F

    Die filetype-list contains all filetypes known to Drop'n Act. A bar
  marks the currently selected filetype. All actions you tigger with the
  gadgets in the lower part of the window affect this type.
    You can select a filetype with your mouse, move the scrollbar to
  scroll through lists that are too large to fit into the window. You
  can also use the key 'F' to select the next type in the list.

    The order of the filetypes is important! Whenever Drop'n Act analyzes
  a file, it does this in the order given in the list. So a self-extracting
  LHX-archive (which is of course a simple AmigaDOS program - otherwise it
  could'n extract itself) would no longer be recognized by Drop'n Act if
  you would put it after the entry 'AmigaDOS program'.
    To move an entry, you can use the gadgets Top, Bottom, Up and Down.


  @{"Back to the menu 'Type-Window'        " LINK TypFenster}
  @{"Back to the menu 'Using Drop'n Act V2'" LINK Bedienung}
  @{"Back to the main menu                 " LINK MAIN}
@endnode

@node Erstes

  I.I.II. The gadget "Top"
  ------------------------

  Shortcut: T

    With the help of this gadget you can move the selected filetype to the
  top of the list.

  See also: @{"Bottom" LINK Letztes}, @{"Up" LINK Hoch} and @{"Down" LINK Runter}.


  @{"Back to the menu 'Type-Window'        " LINK TypFenster}
  @{"Back to the menu 'Using Drop'n Act V2'" LINK Bedienung}
  @{"Back to the main menu                 " LINK MAIN}
@endnode

@node Letztes

  I.I.II. The gadget "Bottom"
  ---------------------------

  Shortcut: B

    With the help of this gadget you can move the selected filetype to the
  bottom of the list.

  See also: @{"Top" LINK Erstes}, @{"Up" LINK Hoch} and @{"Down" LINK Runter}.


  @{"Back to the menu 'Type-Window'        " LINK TypFenster}
  @{"Back to the menu 'Using Drop'n Act V2'" LINK Bedienung}
  @{"Back to the main menu                 " LINK MAIN}
@endnode

@node Hoch

  I.I.IV. The gadget "Up"
  -----------------------

  Shortcut: P

    With the help of this gadget you can move the selected filetype one
  position up.

  See also: @{"Top" LINK Erstes}, @{"Bottom" LINK Letztes} and @{"Down" LINK Runter}.


  @{"Back to the menu 'Type-Window'        " LINK TypFenster}
  @{"Back to the menu 'Using Drop'n Act V2'" LINK Bedienung}
  @{"Back to the main menu                 " LINK MAIN}
@endnode

@node Runter

  I.I.V. The gadget "Down"
  ------------------------

  Shortcut: D

    With the help of this gadgett you can move the selected filetype one position
  down in the list.

  See also: @{"Top" LINK Erstes}, @{"Bottom" LINK Letztes} and @{"Up" LINK Hoch}.


  @{"Back to the menu 'Type-Window'        " LINK TypFenster}
  @{"Back to the menu 'Using Drop'n Act V2'" LINK Bedienung}
  @{"Back to the main menu                 " LINK MAIN}
@endnode

@node TypNeu

  I.I.VI. The gadget "Add"
  ------------------------

  Tastatur-Kürzel: A

    This gadget creates a new filetype with the name "[New Type]". It's not
  yet defined and you'll have to define it first in the @{"Edit-Window" LINK EditFenster}.
  The @{"Edit-Window" LINK EditFenster} can be reached via the @{"Edit-Gadget" LINK Edieren}.


  @{"Back to the menu 'Type-Window'        " LINK TypFenster}
  @{"Back to the menu 'Using Drop'n Act V2'" LINK Bedienung}
  @{"Back to the main menu                 " LINK MAIN}
@endnode

@node LoescheTyp

  I.I.VII. The gadget "Remove"
  ----------------------------

  Shortcut: R

    After selecting this gadget, the currently marked type will be removed
  from the list of filetypes.


  @{"Back to the menu 'Type-Window'        " LINK TypFenster}
  @{"Back to the menu 'Using Drop'n Act V2'" LINK Bedienung}
  @{"Back to the main menu                 " LINK MAIN}
@endnode

@node Edieren

  I.I.VIII. Tne gadget "Edit"
  ---------------------------

  Shortcut: E

    This gadget takes you to the @{"Edit-Window" LINK EditFenster} where you can define
  the current filetype or change its definitions.


  @{"Back to the menu 'Type-Window'        " LINK TypFenster}
  @{"Back to the menu 'Using Drop'n Act V2'" LINK Bedienung}
  @{"Back to the main menu                 " LINK MAIN}
@endnode

@node Shell

  I.I.IX. The gadget "Shell"
  --------------------------

  Shortcut: H

    Some programs make outputs for which there has to be a Shell-window.
  When you click this gadget, a window will open which you can move and
  resize until it fits your liking. Drop'n Act will, whenever it will
  open a shell-window, open the window at this position with these
  dimensions.
    Click this gadget again to close the window.
    If you want Drop'n Act to open a shell window when dealing with a
  certain filetype, you'll have to enable @{"Popup CLI" LINK MitCLI} in the
  @{"Edit-Window" LINK EditFenster}.


  @{"Back to the menu 'Type-Window'        " LINK TypFenster}
  @{"Back to the menu 'Using Drop'n Act V2'" LINK Bedienung}
  @{"Back to the main menu                 " LINK MAIN}
@endnode

@node Save

  I.I.X. The gadget "Save"
  ------------------------

  Shortcut: S

    This gadgets saves all changes you made and quits the preferences
  editor.
    NOTE: The changes aren't recognized by Drop'n Act until you start it
  again or reset your system.


  @{"Back to the menu 'Type-Window'        " LINK TypFenster}
  @{"Back to the menu 'Using Drop'n Act V2'" LINK Bedienung}
  @{"Back to the main menu                 " LINK MAIN}
@endnode

@node Use

  I.I.XI. The gadget "Use"
  ------------------------

  Shortcut: U

    This gadget is much like @{"Save" LINK Save}, but all changes are lost
  after rebooting your system.
    NOTE: The changes aren't recognized by Drop'n Act until you start it
  again.


  @{"Back to the menu 'Type-Window'        " LINK TypFenster}
  @{"Back to the menu 'Using Drop'n Act V2'" LINK Bedienung}
  @{"Back to the main menu                 " LINK MAIN}
@endnode

@node Cancel

  I.I.XII. The gadget "Cancel"
  ----------------------------

  Shortcut: C

    Use this gadget to quit the preferences editor if you don't want to
  save the current changes.


  @{"Back to the menu 'Type-Window'        " LINK TypFenster}
  @{"Back to the menu 'Using Drop'n Act V2'" LINK Bedienung}
  @{"Back to the main menu                 " LINK MAIN}
@endnode

@node Icon

  I.I.XII. The gadget "IconPos"
  -----------------------------

  Shortcut: I

    This gadget opens a small window you can move to any position on your
  Workbench. Drop'n Act will place its AppIcon at the same position the
  next time it's loaded.
    Click this gadget again, and the window will disappear.


  @{"Back to the menu 'Type-Window'        " LINK TypFenster}
  @{"Back to the menu 'Using Drop'n Act V2'" LINK Bedienung}
  @{"Back to the main menu                 " LINK MAIN}
@endnode

