@node Typname

  I.II.I. The gadget "Typename"
  -----------------------------

  Shortcut: T

    Use this gadget to rename the current type. You MUST finish your
  input with the RETURN key.


  @{"Back to the menu 'Edit-Window'        " LINK Bedienung}
  @{"Back to the menu 'Using Drop'n Act V2'" LINK Bedienung}
  @{"Back to the main menu                 " LINK MAIN}
@endnode

@node Liste

  I.II.II. The gadget "List"
  --------------------------

  Shortcut: I

    Every filetype has two lists containing small programs: The
  @{"identify list" LINK Analyse} and the @{"batch list" LINK Batch}.
    This gadget toggles between the two lists.


  @{"Back to the menu 'Edit-Window'        " LINK Bedienung}
  @{"Back to the menu 'Using Drop'n Act V2'" LINK Bedienung}
  @{"Back to the main menu                 " LINK MAIN}
@endnode

@node Skript

  I.II.III. The list "Script"
  ---------------------------

  Shortcut: S

    This list contains the two scripts which belong to a filetype. Every
  change you make always affects the actual line. You can change the actual
  line by clicking on a line. Press the 'S'-key to mark the next line.


  @{"Back to the menu 'Edit-Window'        " LINK Bedienung}
  @{"Back to the menu 'Using Drop'n Act V2'" LINK Bedienung}
  @{"Back to the main menu                 " LINK MAIN}
@endnode

@node Cmd

  I.II.IV. The gadget "Cmd"
  -------------------------

  Shortcut: M

    This gadget assigns a new @{"command" LINK Befehl} to the actual line in the
  @{"script list" LINK Skript}. What happens when you push this button depends
  on whether you're in @{"identify" LINK Analyse} or in @{"batch" LINK Batch} mode.


  @{"Back to the menu 'Edit-Window'        " LINK Bedienung}
  @{"Back to the menu 'Using Drop'n Act V2'" LINK Bedienung}
  @{"Back to the main menu                 " LINK MAIN}
@endnode

@node Argumente

  I.II.V. The gadget "Arguments"
  ------------------------------

  Shortcut: G

    This gadget holds the arguments given to a @{"command" LINK Befehl}. You
  MUST finish your input with the RETURN key.


  @{"Back to the menu 'Edit-Window'        " LINK Bedienung}
  @{"Back to the menu 'Using Drop'n Act V2'" LINK Bedienung}
  @{"Back to the main menu                 " LINK MAIN}
@endnode

@node MitCLI

  I.II.VI. The gadget "Popup CLI"
  -------------------------------

  Shortcut: P

    When this gadget is checked, Drop'n Act opens a shell window whenever
  the batch-list for this filetype is executed.
    If the gadget is NOT checked, though the program makes some output,
  you'll have to add a '>NIL: ' at the beginning of the argument line. If
  you don't, you've won a free journey to India.


  @{"Back to the menu 'Edit-Window'        " LINK Bedienung}
  @{"Back to the menu 'Using Drop'n Act V2'" LINK Bedienung}
  @{"Back to the main menu                 " LINK MAIN}
@endnode

